<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-09T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-09T11:00:00-05:00" n="418" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d418">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/31479:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reed</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos
                                        Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-09T12:00:00-04:00">October 9,
                                1943—noon.</date><lb/>[Received 1:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2389. Caffery’s 4775, October 8, 7 p.m.<note n="52" xml:id="d418fn52">Not
                                printed.</note> Alves certainly seemed very hopeful at 8 o’clock
                            last night when he told me of Ríos’ conversation with Gilbert, reported
                            in my 2388, October 9, 10 a.m.</p>
                        <pb facs="0474" n="462" xml:id="pg_462"/>
                        <p>However, I have just been approached most reluctantly by an Argentine
                            friend who said he was speaking indirectly for President Ramírez and had
                            been asked to inquire of me what United States reaction would be if
                            Argentine Government were to break with Japan only. I declined to
                            express any opinion whatsoever.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Rio.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Reed</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>